# Admin public API integration

This is a **consumer app**. It does **not** own the service catalog / careers data and
must **never query the admin MongoDB directly**. Read everything over the admin's
read-only public HTTP API.

- Base: `ADMIN_PUBLIC_BASE_URL` + `/api/public/...` (see `src/config/constants.js`).
- Business slug: `BUSINESS_SLUG` (`ken-beauty-salon`).
- No auth/cookies/API key. CORS is `*`. Pass `locale` (`en`/`ar`) where supported.
- Errors: `{ code, message, details? }`. Treat 404 `BUSINESS_NOT_FOUND` as "no catalog".

## Implemented endpoints

| Method | Path | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| GET | `/api/public/businesses/{slug}/service-catalog` | Catalog + structured pricing |
| GET | `/api/public/careers/company/{businessSlug}` | Careers board (published jobs) |
| GET | `/api/public/jobs/{slug}` | Job detail + apply form config |
| POST | `/api/public/jobs/{slug}/apply` | Submit application (multipart) |

## Service catalog rules

- `getServiceCatalog(locale, branchId?)` in `src/lib/business/serviceCatalog.js`
  fetches the API (ISR `revalidate: 3600`) and returns `{ businessSlug, total, services }`.
- Response is a **flat list**; build the tree from `parentId` / `categoryIds`, sort by `sortOrder`.
- Only `type === "item"` rows are bookable/priced. Items have `parentId: null` and link via `categoryIds[]`.
- **Prices:** display `priceLabel` verbatim (already localized + currency-suffixed). Raw numeric
  fields carry **no currency** — don't invent one. For `priceDisplayType === "sale"`, strike
  through `priceCompareAtLabel`.

## Cloudinary media

- Catalog nodes carry `imageUrls: string[]` (0–10, `imageUrls[0]` is the cover) and `videoUrl: string|null`.
- URLs are absolute Cloudinary `secure_url`s — use directly in `next/image` / `<video>`. Guard empties.
- Optimize by URL rewrite via `cldTransform(url, "f_auto,q_auto,w_400,c_fit")` in `src/utils/cloudinary.js`
  (no SDK). Use `c_fit` for service media — full image inside the box, no crop or stretch.
  (no SDK). Non-Cloudinary URLs pass through unchanged.
- `next.config.mjs` allows `res.cloudinary.com` with pathname `/**` so any admin cloud renders.

See `docs/PUBLIC_API_INTEGRATION.md` for the full reference.
